pirate /ˈpaɪrɪt/

(pirating,pirated,pirates) 

1. N-COUNT Pirates are sailors who attack other ships and steal property from them. 海盗 

例： In the nineteenth century, pirates roamed the seas. 19世纪，海盗很猖獗。 

2. V-T Someone who pirates CDs, DVDs, books, or computer programs copies and sells them when they have no right to do so. 盗版 (CD、DVD、书籍、计算机程序等) 

例： Computer crimes include data theft and pirating software. 计算机犯罪包括数据窃取和盗版软件。 

3. pirated ADJ 非法复制的 

例： New technology makes it possible to make pirated copies of music and movies. 新技术使制作盗版音乐和影片成为可能。 

4. ADJ A pirate version of something is an illegal copy of it. 盗版的 [ADJ n] 

例： Pirate copies of the DVD are already being sold. 该DVD的盗版已经有售了。

